reviews.review_text: Taped from the parking lot It sounds as if this show was taped from the parking lot.  The mic(s) are so far from the music that at points it seems as if Bobby is whispering.  Its hard to tell if there are any instruments other than Jerry's guitar being played at this performance.  1-star because of quality
It's not that bad It's not that bad I think there is some energy in this show that is not in the other copy and worth listening to.

2 stars???  It's probably not the best sounding aud source of the three posted here but if you sample-stream the jam track before drums you may get the feeling that mr. 1 star cat below had a really tall mama who held him way up  high before dropping him on both ears. Jam after st. 'o circumstance starts off with a hint of terrapin and moves into a jerryless groove that has that 4-17-82 pre-drums flavor, minus the spanish jam. This is a good example of an aud. with a below average rating that deserves more respect.
